comments: LaVine (CHI) makes marginal contact with Thomas (WAS) during his driving shot attempt.
Markkanen (CHI) makes marginal contact with Beal's (WAS) off arm during his driving shot attempt prior to dislodging the ball once it has been released.
Carter Jr. (CHI) does not establish a legal screening position in Bertans' (WAS) path and continues to move into his body affecting his ability to defend.
Carter Jr. (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Thomas (WAS).
Bertans (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Dunn's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Markkanen (CHI) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Beal (WAS) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Brown Jr. (WAS) and LaVine (CHI) briefly engage and disengage off-ball.
After Replay Review, the call on the court of the ball last being touched by Chicago is overturned.

Bertans (WAS) makes contact to LaVine's (CHI) body during his shooting motion that affects his jump shot attempt. LaVine moves through his natural shooting motion on his jump shot attempt and the contact to Bertans' face is incidental.
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Dunn's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.

The illegal contact from Bonga (WAS) that impedes LaVine's (CHI) FOM occurs after the ball has been in bounded but prior to being touched by a player on the court, therefore correctly assessed as a common foul. The contact to Bonga's back from Carter Jr. (CHI) occurs after the foul that was whistled.
Dunn (CHI) cleanly dislodges the ball as he attempts to intercept the inbound pass intended for Beal (WAS).
Thomas (WAS) grabs and pulls LaVine's (CHI) off-arm at the end of the drive and the contact restricts his ability to gather the ball.
Bertans (WAS) and Markkanen (CHI) engage and disengage during the inbound.
Dunn (CHI) briefly places a hand on Mahimni's (WAS) opposite side hip as he engages on the pick then immediately slides it off.
Dunn (CHI) is not in a vertical legal guarding position when he makes contact to Beal's (WAS) arm during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) slightly extends his arms into Bertans (WAS) as he attempts to disengage during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Satoransky (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (WAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Mahinmi (WAS) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by LaVine (CHI).
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Satoransky's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LaVine (CHI) makes contact to Thomas' (WAS) body during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (CHI) places two resting hands to Beal's (WAS) back, but does not extend his arms and the contact is marginal.
Pasecniks (WAS) steps into the lane before the release of the free throw by Carter Jr. (CHI).
Mahinmi (WAS) makes contact to Carter Jr.'s (CHI) body during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Pasecniks (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Satoransky's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Carter Jr. (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
Thomas (WAS) makes marginal contact to LaVine's (CHI) arm at the end of the drive, however he is able to move through the contact and make his desired pass.
Bertans (WAS) makes incidental contact to Carter Jr.'s (CHI) head on the play at the basket and Carter Jr. (CHI) is able to move through the contact and finish at the basket.
Pasecniks (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Harrison's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.

Carter Jr. (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS) and cleanly dislodges the ball off his forearm.  Any contact to Beal's arm after the dislodge is deemed incidental.
LaVine (CHI) and Thomas (WAS) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Harrison (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
